一个理性的人爱上航海，这是我做的最疯狂的事——对话徐京坤http://www.infzm.com/contents/258538 <div>;<i>;2023-10-16 15:00:00</i>;</div>;<p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/ 10/11/e8ZUobY9rhBEcl4R2T5EDttgP3LOyDzNF0griYOd.jpg" border="0" width="960" height="720" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/e8ZUobY9rhBEcl4R2T5EDttgP3LOyDzNF0 griYOd. jpg" data-key="253645">;</p>; <p style="color: #999; text-align: center;">;"In 2021, I will come to Brittany again to start my IMOCA plan. Offshore sailing is still in its infancy in China. Due to budget constraints, I once again live on my boat, but this time my boat is 60 feet"<span style="color: #aaa;">;(Interview Provided by the author/picture)</span>;</p>; <p>;When there are friends around him, Xu Jingkun is often a listener. "I seem to have very few friends of the same age. All the friends I have are older brothers." He likes to listen to big brothers. The buddies chatted about everything, "You can learn a lot."</p>; <p>;In the past two years, the eldest buddies often got together because of his return to China, and the topics mostly revolved around him and his circumnavigation and transatlantic sailing race. And his IMOCA60 super racing boat. </p>; <p>;Even if everyone is talking about himself, Xu Jingkun is still used to silence. When he is not talking, his face, which has been tanned by the sun all year round, looks particularly calm. "Actually, I often do this at sea. I don't speak, but I enjoy it in my heart. The lack of expression does not mean that I am unhappy, but I have such a habit of being 'lazy in talking'."</p>; <p>;He said that he is a "Stupid", this is absolutely not the case. He is sensitive, humble and well-measured. When we politely asked the eldest brother to "exit" and started a two-and-a-half-hour in-depth conversation in a big brother's quiet and undisturbed office, he opened himself up to us with accurate and moving expressions. </p>; <p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/VjJv1LH5mWRi07GYyWBWZYHqxoQfW4ugxzvvUdSq.jpg" border="0" width="720" height= "960" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/VjJv1LH5mWRi07GYyWBWZYHqxoQfW4ugxzvvUdSq.jpg" data-key="253638">;</p>; <p style="color : #999; text-align: center;">;Xu Jingkun's old childhood photos, the accident has not happened yet, he is a lively and healthy mountain child<span style="color: #aaa;">;(provided by the interviewee/picture)< /span>;</p>; <h4>;Sailing makes me feel comfortable, which is the biggest gain</h4>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: italics , Italics_GB2312, STKaiti;">;When did you feel particularly comfortable and at ease? Many disabled people use sleeves to cover their missing parts, or wear prosthetics when going out, but you just naturally expose your left arm and even use it as a hand or an arm. </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;Yes, I am very calm and I am very free. When I first started training at Shandong Sports School, it was not possible. Even though you were training as a disabled athlete, when others looked at you, you would feel uncomfortable and nervous yourself. Later, I joined the national sailing team and slowly began to change. But what really liberated me was that after the national team was disbanded, I started sailing on my own. </span>;</p>; <p>;Sailing really changed me completely. When many people talk about me, they always say that I am successful now and have changed my destiny. In fact, the biggest gain for me is this kind of freedom. Sailing makes me live very freely. I can choose what I want and my current situation, which is very good. </p>; <p>;From the time I decided to sail, from the time I first sailed around the China Sea, my life began to change. Whether it's loneliness at sea, wind and waves, or even some fears sometimes, after you experience it too much, you will gain that kind of freedom and become very comfortable, not caring about external things or what others think. In this way It's very comfortable to be alive. </p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: KaiTi, KaiTi_GB2312, STKaiti;">;What do you think of the "one-armed captain" given to you by others? Label? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;I gave it to myself, haha. When Ajiu (<span style="font-family: 楷体, 楷体_GB2312, STKaiti;">;Xu Jingkun’s wife and partner Xiao Shuyao</span>;) wrote my biography "The Humble Dreamer", I told She, you need to write "one-armed captain" in the title. The media teachers we have contacted over the years are also very professional. Many times they will ask very politely, "Shouldn't we write like this, or what kind of title is more appropriate?" I will tell them to just write " One-armed Captain". I don’t think there’s anything that shouldn’t be said. On the contrary, one-armedness is a very unique thing about me. </span>;</p>; <p>;You dare to face it only if you dare to speak, right? I don’t care about this at all now. In fact, there is no need to talk about whether I care or not. If you are still thinking about whether you care or not, it means you still care. (Laughs) Let’s put it this way, I think my left arm is great. When I have children in the future, I will be the most unique father in their eyes, which is cool. </p>; <p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/NxSHzppQbBvqiojKcnTyOurdXvkbp7ctiri8h4p6.jpg" border="0" width="960" height= "636" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/NxSHzppQbBvqiojKcnTyOurdXvkbp7ctiri8h4p6.jpg" data-key="253637">;</p>; <p style="color : #999; text-align: center;">;Xu Jingkun used this J24 to start a circumnavigation of the China Sea from the northernmost point to the southernmost point of China. It was the first ship in his life and also his first time. Solo voyage<span style="color: #aaa;">;(provided by interviewee/picture)</span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style=" font-family: Kaiti, Kaiti_GB2312, STKaiti;">;It is not easy for you to fully reconcile with the accidental injury caused by the explosion when you were 12 years old. </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;Yes, this matter has completely turned over and is completely over. The damage and shadow in my life have been completely wiped out. Expelled. This is what sailing has brought me, including my growth and experiences along the way. I am very lucky! An accidental injury is like a devil appearing in life. It wants to hurt me, but before it can really hurt me, I have already defeated it. </span>;</p>; <p>;Looking back now, I can feel that if I had not stepped out in time to defeat it, I would most likely have been defeated by it. I can also feel that many friends with physical disabilities have been deeply hurt physically and mentally due to their disability, and I always want to give them some encouragement. </p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: KaiTi, KaiTi_GB2312, STKaiti;">;Many people outside the sailing circle know you from "Ten In that episode of "Three Invitations", when you were talking to teacher Xu Zhiyuan, you said that you "have never felt at ease in the first half of your life." What time are you in now? Is it the previous life or the next life? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;It’s still the first half of my life, and I’m still not at ease. I actually don’t have particularly big ambitions, I just don’t like falling to the bottom. The so-called bottom does not mean material life. I am very adaptable to life. Now I still often only eat two meals a day. It’s not that I don’t have money, but that I don’t have time. I have a lot of work to do on the ship, and it’s very troublesome if the work at hand is interrupted. I would rather finish it without eating. If you don't like the bottom, you don't like the feeling of having no goals and not being able to control your own life. </span>;</p>; <p>;After setting the goal of participating in the 2024 Vendée Globe, life has become a battle. The Solo Transatlantic at Rum Road in 2022 and the Double Transatlantic at Café Road in 2023 are all aimed at qualifying for the Vendée Globe. We don’t have the financial resources to take our time, so we can only treat one season as 3 seasons and one person as For 10 people, our team only has 5 people, and the German team has 50 people. </p>; <p>;Because this is my own goal and I like this goal, I don’t feel how hard life is or how big my sacrifice is. Most people would have a hard time adapting to my life and would suffer to death, but I think this is the life I dream of. In a very beautiful pier, on a very good racing boat, doing what I most want to do, doing my own professional things, without being dominated, commanded or controlled by anyone, I think this is very good, right Bar? </p>; <p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/ps9YjERLoV0uQbWm6Z3XYKpkeQoZib9Sx4Oymdk1.jpg" border="0" width="1436" height= "1078" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/ps9YjERLoV0uQbWm6Z3XYKpkeQoZib9Sx4Oymdk1.jpg" data-key="253639">;</p>; <p style="color : #999; text-align: center;">;On the way around the China Sea, Xu Jingkun once fell into the water and drifted to Dongyin Island in Taiwan, China. When Xu Jingkun left, local children brought him rare candy milk on the island to see him off< span style="color: #aaa;">;(provided by the interviewee/picture)</span>;</p>; <h4>;I am a "stupid person"</h4>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly ：</strong>;<span style="font-family: 楷体, 凯体_GB2312, STKaiti;">;What attracts you most about sailing? Is it the thrill of adventure? The freedom of going deep into the ocean away from the crowd, or the desire to return to the mainland and embrace family and friends after fighting the waves? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun:</strong>;<span>;Actually, I am also trying to understand myself on a deeper level. What do I want? </span>;</p>; <p>;Navigation is even contrary to my nature. I am very cautious and cautious. I like a room with doors and windows tightly closed so that no thief can sneak in. But sailing is always exposed to wind. No matter how well-prepared you are on the shore, situations will always arise at sea, and you have to hold your "shield" to resist them on all sides. It's very embarrassing. I actually don't like that kind of accident. </p>; <p>;I'm not that romantic either. There is a kind of person who really likes the solitude of sailing on the sea, such as the legendary French navigator Bernard. He was disgusted with cities and crowds. He loved freedom and sailing crazily and enjoyed solitude. I'm not that kind of person, I'm not that crazy. I am a "fake lunatic", and I am not the artistic type. When I'm at sea, I always miss my family and friends on the shore. I want to drink beer and have barbecue with them when we dock. </p>; <p>;Whether I was a professional athlete on the national sailing team or am now engaged in extreme sailing competitions, I do not have a competitive mentality that insists on winning championships, advocating gold medals and winner takes all. Some people who compete in extreme sailing competitions participate in the competition just to win. Their competitive strategies are very aggressive. If they cannot win, they may choose to quit the competition. Neither am I. </p>; <p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/yST5LtCmWEI4dPPdC6KCdhDzm7YrmfK5wjv3OAfV.jpg" border="0" width="960" height= "720" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/yST5LtCmWEI4dPPdC6KCdhDzm7YrmfK5wjv3OAfV.jpg" data-key="253642">;</p>; <p style="color : #999; text-align: center;">;On September 19, 2015, Duarnenez, the one-man transatlantic extreme sailing race, set sail. Dream was the first to break out of the starting line. Friends dressed in local clothes came to see Xu Jingkun off<span style ="color: #aaa;">;(provided by the interviewee/picture)</span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: italics, Italics_GB2312, STKaiti;">;You are not crazy, you are very rational. Sailing seems like the craziest thing you, a rational person, could do. </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;Yes, I am very rational. But he seems to be doing something very irrational and crazy. He sailed around the China Sea and around the world, crossed the Atlantic Ocean in a 6.5-meter boat, and now bought a racing boat to participate in the world's most difficult extreme circumnavigation race. </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: KaiTi, KaiTi_GB2312, STKaiti;">;It can only mean that you really like this thing . As a rational person, you can devote so much to sailing. To you, this is really crazy to the extreme. </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;Yes, that’s true. The life we ​​live now is a complete state of madness. After crossing the Atlantic in a single-person boat in 2015, it was actually considered top-notch in China. At that time, I was working as the vice president of a yacht club in Shenzhen, and my income and treatment were very good. Let’s put aside the good life, from 2017 to 2020, I completed a three-year circumnavigation with Ah Jiu. After that, we had a pretty good time in Hainan, and I had the goal of participating in the Vendée Globe. </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: KaiTi, KaiTi_GB2312, STKaiti;">;Qingdao has many sailing talents, and they have already gone before you There are several legends, why can you go further and further, especially starting your own journey to the world's top professional rowing captain in 2022? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;I am a "stupid person"! On the one hand, I am very rational, and on the other hand, I don’t think too much about anything. When I think something is good and worth doing, I won’t think about doing this or not doing that, or not doing it. How about doing this and that...</span>;</p>; <p>;After I bought the IMOCA60 racing boat, I started to think about it, because I started to analyze rationally: I am a person from an ordinary peasant family, and every year Not making this money, but spending so much money...that's it. </p>; <p>;It costs 15,000 euros to lift the boat from the shore into the water, so there is no test drive. After paying the money, I got on the boat for the first time. It really felt unreal. It was completely different from all the boats I had sailed before. When that boat was flying on the sea, I saw why it was called the world's top racing boat. "I finally stood on this boat, and this boat belongs to us!" This feeling just rose in my heart, I felt a lot of pressure in the next second. There are so many cable accessories on this super racing boat, it is really difficult to learn in a short time, and an operating error will cause huge losses. </p>; <p>;I saw it was too complicated and thought it was impossible to solve it. After taking over, I never left the ship. I parked it on the dock and studied it every day. It took two months before I went to sea alone. </p>; <p>;I am not a very smart person, and I am very forgetful. I can’t figure out what I thought and calculated when I bought the boat. Forget it, we don’t want to think about it anymore, let’s talk about it tomorrow, tomorrow we will forget these things again, and you don’t want to think about it anymore. </p>; <p>;I like mechanical things, and I may have a little talent for boats. Our racing boat is very complicated. Many captains in Europe have engineering degrees, and they also have teams and coaches. I bought the boat by myself. I haven't graduated from junior high school, and I'm self-taught in English, but I'm not afraid, I can figure it out even if I spend some time. </p>; <p>;My experience with racing boats is pleasant most of the time, but it is too expensive and the maintenance bills are expensive. I feel distressed every time I have to pay a bill, but my rationality tells me to pay it quickly, and then forget about this unhappiness, haha. </p>; <p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/x2HEJrLwLBk7baJ6HnQgmSBo8lwDGmiNb3L1ZLHG.jpg" border="0" width="960" height= "720" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/x2HEJrLwLBk7baJ6HnQgmSBo8lwDGmiNb3L1ZLHG.jpg" data-key="253650">;</p>; <p style="color : #999; text-align: center;">;In Madagascar, Xu Jingkun gave the ship’s batteries to local schools that had no electricity. All the children in the village followed him through the village <span style="color: #aaa;">;(provided by the interviewee/picture)</span>;</p>; <h4>;I want to be my own little hero< /h4>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: 楷体, 凯体_GB2312, STKaiti;">;We ordinary people will feel happy when we are close to the sea. Are you right? The feelings of the sea are a little more complicated than ours. It seems that there is no way to easily and simply say "I like the sea"? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;I really have to think about the emotional connection between me and the sea. For a long time, I actually had no time to think. This state made me particularly uncomfortable. Maritime navigation is my job, and I like this project myself, but this matter really makes me very tired now. I feel a little resistant when I think of going back to France, which is like a battlefield. </span>;</p>; <p>;I want to find a rational reason, I don’t want to easily say why I like it and why I don’t like it. I need to think about it, and I want to find a real answer that I feel comfortable with. </p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: 楷体, 毷体_GB2312, STKaiti;">;Global sailing and extreme transoceanic racing are completely different. In extreme racing, you face multiple pressures on funds and speed, as well as the formulation and execution of competition strategies. You cannot enjoy the voyage and the sea like you can when sailing around the world. Will the happy experience of sailing around the world for three years help you in this high-pressure period, so that you will always have feelings for the sea and sailing, so that it will not be all the pressure and consumption caused by the competition? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;Indeed. Sailing between the sky and the sea is a very wonderful enjoyment. I have been to so many places where the sea is connected, and everything I see and experience makes people feel wonderful. But I may actually prefer the specific sense of goal of extreme sailing competitions. If I keep floating on the sea, I will not be satisfied. </span>;</p>; <p>;I am a perfectionist and a bit heroic. I don’t mean to be a superhero who saves the earth alone. I want to be my own little hero. Withstanding the pressure and crossing the sea during extreme sailing, I feel like a little hero every time I come back after completing it. </p>; <p>;For me, from the arduous preparation before the start of the season, to the high pressure after the start, to the release when I finally arrive at the shore, it is the process that I enjoy the most. </p>; <p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/PRfAyTagmNJJWaGCsrssaVZ8gjAGh0PyPOXZ40sm.jpg" border="0" width="960" height= "720" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/PRfAyTagmNJJWaGCsrssaVZ8gjAGh0PyPOXZ40sm.jpg" data-key="253651">;</p>; <p style="color : #999; text-align: center;">;Meet musicians from all over the world and catch up with the Hiwa Festival in Tahiti. The street band's performance makes sailors unable to help but dance<span style="color: #aaa ;">;(provided by the interviewee/picture)</span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: 楷体, 凯体_GB2312, STKaiti; ">;In addition to a sense of freedom and accomplishment, how has sailing shaped your personality? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun:</strong>;<span>;Sailing has expanded my physical ability and will. My body is particularly good, which was developed under extreme requirements. I can feel the strong adaptability and recovery ability of my body, and the limits of my body are stimulated in the extreme environment. This is why I particularly like sailing. I can feel that I am a strong person among human beings. For me, this makes me stronger inside. </span>;</p>; <p>;Sailing is not about romantic yearning or blind bravery. You have to complete the extreme challenge, bring the racing boat back safely, and go ashore to give your waiting family a hug. A lot of specific and hard work needs to be done to get the boat in perfect condition before setting off. Any problems must be taken into consideration, and there are two or more sets of prepared contingency plans. Sailing has allowed me to develop a strong execution ability. "I do what I say". No matter how high the goal is, I will put in more effort. This is also engraved in my bones. Take everything seriously and never leave it at that. </p>; <p>;After experiencing the loneliness and wind and waves of sailing alone, I prefer daily life and love my environment and friends from the bottom of my heart. Calm, stable, storm-free daily life like now makes people cherish it, and makes people want to praise the beautiful weather and beautiful atmosphere. </p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: 楷体, 凯体_GB2312, STKaiti;">;You have had very lonely and difficult days, and you often have one when you are a teenager The fear and hopelessness of falling to the bottom of nowhere. When I set sail alone to circumnavigate the China Sea in 2012, I was filled with resentment as I feared that I would die. After so many years of sailing, have you made peace with yourself and your destiny? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun:</strong>;<span>;At that time in 2012, I really felt like I was gambling with my fate, and I had a feeling in my heart that once a hero is gone, he will never return. That kind of tragic, even with some resentment, asking why my life has to be so difficult, if you don't believe me, I will fight to the death, I want to make this happen, yes, with this kind of energy. </span>;</p>; <p>;Now that these have been healed, it is very important to me to complete each goal one by one. You will slowly know that you can control your own destiny. When I was a child in the countryside, I lost half of my arm. I was surrounded by an environment where I really had no goals and my life was aimless. You don’t know where your goal is, and you have never achieved a goal. You will hate the cowardly and vulnerable self, and long to be full of fighting spirit and courage. </p>; <p>;Through sailing, I have one goal after another, which is also a process of self-healing and growth. </p>; <p>;Since I spent more than 7 months repairing a small boat that was about to be scrapped, named it "Dream", and achieved the first goal of circumnavigating the China Sea, I learned to believe in myself, Believe in the dream. In fact, if I failed that time, I might never get up again in this life, and I might be completely defeated. Not only was I defeated by external things, but my own line of defense was also gone. Looking back now, I really feel that it was understandable for others to say that I was unrealistic. I can say that I was too lucky. That beginning made me learn to believe, and this belief helped me step by step to get to where I am now. </p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: 楷体, 凯体_GB2312, STKaiti;">;Sail offshore, deep into the heart of the sea, on both sides of the mainland How would you feel about a scene like that at 1,500 nautical miles? Is the sea kind or malicious to sailors? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;I actually don’t have any special literary feelings. For my racing boat, I am not afraid when I am in the middle of the ocean. Its safety performance is very good. It is designed to fight against storms. As long as you don't make mistakes in operation, it is very safe. On the contrary, if it is close to the coast, fishing nets, passing ships and other things will pose a threat to the boat. </span>;</p>; <p>;The sea has no good intentions or malice. It has no intention of harming you. It exists objectively according to the laws of nature. People naturally calm down and become less cynical at sea. To be honest, I think I am more afraid of people. Sometimes I am too busy with sailing matters to not read the news, and my mind is very calm. When I pay attention to social news, I feel at a loss. The rules set by Western society are for the East, and the East must make some checks and balances against the West, right? Many things do not have an objective rule, they are mixed together and extremely complicated. </p>; <p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/sHh7XjhhF6fTr6VquWLzIvx8bI30sFUYjc6vvFgX.jpg" border="0" width="960" height= "640" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/11/sHh7XjhhF6fTr6VquWLzIvx8bI30sFUYjc6vvFgX.jpg" data-key="253647">;</p>; <p style="color : #999; text-align: center;">;Xu Jingkun and British captain Mike Godin cooperated in sea trial<span style="color: #aaa;">;(provided by interviewee/picture)</span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: 楷体, 凯体_GB2312, STKaiti;">;The outside world has extremely high expectations of you, and you are very demanding of yourself. You also know that your rubber band has been stretched very tight. In the process of entering and completing the 2024 Vendée Globe, what changes will you make to make yourself more relaxed and calm, so as not to be broken? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun:</strong>;<span>;Actually, I have started to make adjustments now, because I know that this thing is indeed too stressful and will really put people under pressure. Broken. </span>;</p>; <p>;The premise for adjustment is that the boat must be in perfect condition. If I take good care of the boat on the shore, then the boat can take good care of me in the deep sea. This is for sure. The coffee road race is about to start, and all the racing teams are very busy, but I can go back to China to rest and recuperate because I have done a lot of work day and night and the boat is already in the best condition. </p>; <p>;I also made some adjustments in my life. For a period of time, we lived on the boat to facilitate our work. Foreigners were also surprised to see us. The two Chinese people were working in the morning and evening. I just rented a house some time ago and my life is a little more normal. For a while, the pressure was so great that I was disgusted by the sight of the boat and lost the fun. I knew in my heart that this would definitely not work. </p>; <p>;Faced with the next devilish voyage like the Vendée Globe, if you don’t have sincere love, sincere faith, and lose your original intention, you won’t be able to persevere. </p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: 楷体, 凯体_GB2312, STKaiti;">;Vendée Global is known as the "Mount Everest of the Sea". The most difficult extreme sailing event on earth, your current goal is still to successfully obtain the ticket for the Vendée Globe. When you finally successfully complete the Vendée and return to your daily life without such specific and clear goals, you will be there At that time, having completed the most difficult competition goal, are you confident that you can devote yourself to ordinary life? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun: </strong>;<span>;It is true that I have this problem. Every time I complete a competition goal, after I stop, sometimes I don’t know how to deal with things in life. </span>;</p>; <p>;My talent is that I can manage a single thing well. I build this boat to the extreme and do it very well. I go all out and do not be lazy or slippery. This is A character of mine. But as soon as I return to life, I need to deal with some rules. Sometimes I feel that it is unfair and it makes me very uncomfortable. I don’t like to be suppressed, but sometimes you are unable to resist, including when it comes to personnel matters. I'm very insensitive to people. </p>; <p>;For example, if you look at the many good friends and elder brothers I have, in fact, every time I come back, I often neglect to bring them something or pay more attention to them and give back. I'm a retarded person in this regard. I often remember that I didn't bring anything with me until I arrived at someone's door. It's not like you don't understand this kind of worldliness. You understand it now that you're older, but it's always too late when you react. , life is always not so bright. </p>; <p>;<strong>;Southern People Weekly:</strong>;<span style="font-family: KaiTi, KaiTi_GB2312, STKaiti;">;Coffee Road You partnered with the legendary British captain Mike Godin, The qualifying voyage of 1,200 nautical miles is 17 hours faster than last year’s Rum Road qualifying event. Mike has participated in the Vendée three times and won runner-up on the Café Road ten times. You are becoming more and more skilled in sailing. In addition to participating in and completing the race, do you have any higher expectations for the ranking? </span>;</p>; <p>;<strong>;Xu Jingkun:</strong>;<span>;From my own ability and boat racing ability, I can indeed hit faster speeds. My boat is still Only 70% of the performance was released, and it was not pushed to the limit. But our strategy is to finish the race safely and get points. To be honest, I don't even have the money for a major repair, and I don't have the capital to run around. </span>;</p>; <p>;I have also clearly communicated this with Captain Mike Godin. He understands very well. He has also experienced this kind of difficult period with limited funds. The strategy is very clear, but it will still be a challenge to implement it without making mistakes. I remind myself every day not to be radical and not to be too quick! Must be slow, must be cautious! But many times at sea, decisions are made in a split second. At that moment, it is difficult to say that what you think is the right decision is truly wise. I hope that my partner and I can work well together and achieve a good balance in specific situations. </p>; <p>;</p>; Mon, 16 Oct 2023 15:25:03 +0800 
遭“恐袭预告”，法国缘何被恐怖组织盯上？http://www.infzm.com/contents/258676 <div>;<i>;2023-10-16 12:52:55</i>;</div>;<p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/ 10/16/Dvkztk8oPl2cxtEL0mOldqVov5K6Q99PqsajhnCD.jpg" border="0" width="1700" height="1133" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/16/Dvkztk8oPl2cxtEL0mOldqVov5K 6Q99PqsajhnCD. jpg" data-key="254136">;</p>; <p style="color: #999; text-align: center;">;On October 13, 2023 local time, a man holding a knife in Arras, France Killed a teacher and wounded two others at a high school. Counter-terrorism officials said they were leading an investigation into the knife attack. <span style="color: #aaa;">;(Visual China/Photo)</span>;</p>; <p>;At a time when the international situation is extremely tense, terrorism strikes France again. </p>; <p>;On October 13, 2023 local time, after a knife attack occurred in the northern city of Arras, France stated that it was on terror alert and raised the threat level to the highest level. The attack left one teacher dead and three others seriously injured. </p>; <p>;Just one day later, France’s Louvre Museum, Palace of Versailles, Lyon Train Station and other landmark buildings issued “emergency evacuation orders” due to security threats. Some Louvre museum visitors posted on social media that loud sirens were heard during the evacuation. </p>; <p>;Just last month, Al Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula issued a "terrorist attack warning" to France and Sweden through an internal publication. French Interior Minister Gérald Darmanin said in an exclusive interview with L'Ouest-France that the authorities would respond as seriously as ever because "the risk of terrorism remains high." </p>; <p>;The fear of the "11.13 Paris terrorist attacks" many years ago came to mind. Why is France always targeted by terrorists? </p>; <h4>;<strong>;The risk of terrorist attacks has revived</strong>;</h4>; <p>;Eight years ago, after the "11.13 Paris terrorist attacks", people took to the streets and stood at the site of the attack. Place condolence candles and flowers. </p>; <p>;On the evening of November 17, 2015, at the memorial site near the Rue des Fountains de la King in Paris, photographer Benjamin Filarski spotted a sad policeman leaning on the shoulders of his colleagues among the mourning crowd. Crying. </p>; <p>;Benjamin seized the opportunity and pressed the shutter, freezing the heartbreaking scene. He posted the photo on social media, titled "Crying Police." </p>; <p>;Eight years later, this scene of police crying, which represented the painful memory of France, appeared in a new round of "terrorist attack notices". </p>; <p>;According to a report by French Commercial FMTV (BFMTV) on September 14, Al Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula (AQAP) issued a "terrorist threat" to France and Sweden in its latest publication "Voice of Combat" . </p>; <p>;In a propaganda poster published by Al-Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula (AQAP), a masked man is holding a long gun and looking down from a high position. Under cold eyes, two French policemen hugged each other and cried. </p>; <p>;It is understood that the article of the promotional material was disseminated through a variety of Internet platforms. The article also suggested that after a series of scripture-burning incidents, Sweden "led the EU countries in combating Islam and Muslim countries." </p>; <p>;Al Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula is a radical Islamist organization mainly active in Yemen and Saudi Arabia. After the terrorist attack on Charlie Hebdo in Paris in January 2015, the organization "claimed responsibility." </p>; <p>;“犯罪前科”与赤裸裸的挑衅，引发了法国当局的担忧。 </p>; <p>;“很长一段时间里，我们以为这种情况不会再次发生。然而阿富汗、黎凡特和非洲等正在为其提供资金，这意味着威胁可能发生。”2023年9月20日，法国内政部长达尔马宁在受访时警告，该国的恐袭风险可能死灰复燃。 </p>; <p>;达尔马宁指出，目前主要的危险仍然来自法国本土的激进分子。这些人通常是在互联网上逐步激进化，他们极度孤立，乐于接受圣战宣传，响应仇恨号召。由于宗教激进化、模仿或精神脆弱等原因，他们使用非常有限的手段实施行动。 </p>; <p>;同时，基地组织和“伊斯兰国”分支在一些地区重建。在萨赫勒地区，尤其是在黎凡特和阿富汗，毒品网络正在重建，并有可能为恐怖主义提供资金。 </p>; <p>;“有了钱，这些组织就可以通过渗透移民潮等方式，就地培训圣战分子。就像2015 年11 月13 日袭击事件中的一些行凶者一样。他们还可以远程培训其他人。”达尔马宁说。 </p>; <h4>;<strong>;罩袍禁令</strong>;<strong>;拉锯战</strong>;</h4>; <p>;据法国BFMTV 9月15日报道，该恐怖组织呼吁“让穆斯林儿童独处”“在父母的保护下成长”。这段文字，加上针对“巴黎某个部级政府部门”的威胁，暗示基地组织指的是与最近法国国内的“Abaya禁令”相关。 </p>; <p>;“很难不把它与最近法国学校禁止穿Abaya联系起来，尽管根本没有提到这一点。”报道称。 </p>; <p>;阿巴雅（Abaya）是一种宽松的长袍，可以遮罩女性身体曲线。在法国学校中，常常可以看到女性穆斯林学生穿着阿巴雅上学。 </p>; <p>;2023年8月末，法国政府以政教分离原则为由，禁止学生穿这种有着明显宗教标志的服装。据教育部门指令，9月开学时，穿阿巴雅到校的学生禁止进入课室，之后由校方向她们“解释禁令的意义所在”。 </p>; <p>;法国总统马克龙在此项问题上强调，政府在这个关系世俗主义原则的问题上“绝不让步”。他表示，“我们知道会有违规的情况出现……有些或许只出于一时疏忽，但相当一部分是想要挑战共和价值。我们决不能妥协。”</p>; <p>;尽管法国政府就禁令表现出了强硬姿态，但依然有穆斯林学生身穿罩袍到校。 </p>; <p>;据法国教育部统计，9月4日开学时，全国有298名学生穿着罩袍上学，其中只有67名学生坚持不愿脱掉罩袍。 </p>; <p>;当地时间9月7日，法国克莱蒙费朗高中一名女孩因坚持穿着罩袍上学而被禁止入校。随后，女孩父亲向校长发出了“割喉”死亡威胁。校长报警后，该名家长当晚被警方扣留。 </p>; <p>;除了学生群体外，也有很多穆斯林支持者以多种方式反对“罩袍禁令”。 </p>; <p>;法国政府颁布禁令后，包括巴黎南方教育协会在内的三家机构提出上诉，他们要求中止禁令，称禁令违反了“基本自由”。 </p>; <p>;2023年9月19日，十多名穆斯林女性聚集在法国驻奥地利大使馆门外，就阿巴雅禁令对法国穆斯林妇女表示声援。在线传播的抗议视频中可以看到，一位身穿橘色长袍、头戴头巾的女性高举抗议标牌，上面写着“Abaya，我们的身份，我们的权利”。 </p>; <p>;“法国的穆斯林政策，其实是其针对所有族群公民基本要求的组成部分。”上海外国语大学中东研究所研究员钮松告诉南方周末记者，就宗教服饰而言，其所涉及的也不只是头巾问题，其他宗教包括基督教的相关服饰或标志也在限制之列。 </p>; <p>;“换言之，法国在公共领域对于宗教服饰、标志的限制，并不是针对特定的宗教，但宗教信仰者的抗争也一直伴随着政策推行的过程。即便是法国社会内部，也存在着对共和同化与政教分离原则的理解和执行方法上的不同看法。总之，围绕头巾、abaya服装的激烈对抗不仅撕裂了法国社会，而且也必然激怒保守的穆斯林群体。”钮松说。 </p>; <p>;争论持续多日后，法国最高法院9月25日作出裁定，政府对穆斯林服饰长袍的禁令是“合乎法律”的。 </p>; <h4>;<strong>;为什么</strong>;<strong>;总</strong>;<strong>;是法国？ </strong>;</h4>; <p>;2015-2016年，法国巴塔克兰音乐厅枪击案、《查理周刊》袭击案等接连发生，暴力恐怖袭击愈演愈烈。 </p>; <p>;2016年7月14日，造成至少84人死亡的“尼斯海岸恐袭案”发生后，英国安全智库“现实主义研究地缘政治与安全中心（CGSRS）”刊发名为《为什么总是法国》的报告，试图分析法国境内恐袭高发的内在逻辑。 </p>; <p>;报告称，虽然其他欧洲国家也经历过恐怖主义，但是“法国正在呈现出一种明显的模式”“受到的影响尤为严重”。同时，虽然袭击者宣称“效忠极端组织”，但大多数人都是年轻的法国公民，且呈现小团体式活动。 </p>; <p>;为什么法国成为本土伊斯兰恐怖主义如此突出的目标？报告对此作出了多个解释。 </p>; <p>;首先是外交政策。报告称，法国长期以来一直干预穆斯林世界，特别是中东和北非（MENA）地区。因而伊斯兰主义者经常把法国视为“合法目标”。 </p>; <p>;其次，法国人口构成增加了伊斯兰恐怖袭击的可能性，比如7%-9%的人口是穆斯林，远高于德国或英国等其他欧洲大国。 </p>; <p>;此外，来自中东和北非地区的移民缺少流动机会，长期生活在贫困之中，由此带来对法国本土人民和机构的“不信任和仇恨”。最后，法国有着悠久的世俗主义传统，许多公民对任何形式的宗教都持非常消极的看法。这让一些穆斯林群体感到宗教自由受到了攻击。 </p>; <p>;对于法国缘何被极端组织“盯上”，多名中国国际关系学者也向南方周末记者作出解释。 </p>; <p>;钮松认为，在西方阵营内部，法国针对多元族群和信仰群体的态度较为“严苛”，强调族群平等并捍卫世俗化原则，不允许宗教元素在公共领域过分展示。因此，围绕头巾问题、abaya服饰问题等所产生的矛盾与冲突便会周期性呈现。 </p>; <p>;此外，外来移民、难民与欧洲社会存在着结构性矛盾，这既包括经济实力上的显著差距，更包括文明背景上的迥异。德国与意大利等国对穆斯林移民的态度与政策相对温和，而法国因其严格的世俗化政策而更容易在宗教服饰等问题上激化早已累积的矛盾，并因问题的涉教性而难有回旋余地。法国自然成为恐怖组织在欧洲展开袭击的“优先”选项。 </p>; <p>;中国人民大学国际事务研究所所长王义桅告诉南方周末记者，法国是近代欧洲文明的发源地。法国大革命的自由、平等、博爱理念影响了整个欧洲。但是，自由的泛滥也带来了对其他文明的冒犯，这会引起保守主义者的不满。同时，法国穆斯林人口众多，针对外部穆斯林世界的行为也会引起内部的反弹。 </p>; <p>;正如《为什么总是法国》报告中预测，“由于问题的复杂性和深度，法国未来可能面临更多恐怖袭击”。 </p>; <h4>;<strong>;“</strong>;<strong>;这</strong>;<strong>;不是新鲜事</strong>;<strong>;”</strong>;</h4>; <p>;除了法国外，瑞典也是这场“恐袭预告”中的袭击对象。这与瑞典国内数月来激进主义者焚烧经书风波有关。 </p>; <p>;自2023年6月起，瑞典多地发生焚烧、亵渎伊斯兰宗教典籍事件，主要参与者为伊拉克难民萨尔万·莫米卡（Salwan Momika）和萨尔万·纳吉姆（Salwan Najem）。 </p>; <p>;二人多次公开反对伊斯兰宗教典籍《古兰经》，并举行示威活动。 </p>; <p>;其实，在这次“恐袭预告”之前，瑞典就因“烧经”事件被其他极端组织“点名”恐吓。 </p>; <p>;2023年8月，基地组织媒体平台“As-Sahab 媒体基金会”（The As-Sahab Media Foundation）在一份题为“攻击侵略民族的义务”的公告中呼吁，对丹麦和瑞典在过去几个月中发生的焚烧经书行为展开“报复”。 </p>; <p>;8月13日，英国外交部发布出行警告，称瑞典很有可能发生袭击事件，其安全当局已挫败了多起袭击企图。中国驻瑞典使馆也提醒，中国公民应关注瑞典当前安全形势变化，提高安全意识，保持高度警惕，加强安全防范。 </p>; <p>;8月17日，瑞典将该国恐怖主义威胁等级从3级提升至4级“高威胁状态”，这是2016年以来的首次。 </p>; <p>;瑞典当局称，这一决定是基于瑞典安全形势不断恶化而作出的“综合性、长期性和战略性判断”。此后，瑞典多个部门在边境、机场、公共交通等多领域加强安全措施。 </p>; <p>;对于瑞典遇到的“恐袭威胁”，英国国王学院瑞典恐怖主义研究员汉斯·布鲁恩（Hans Brun）认为，这些威胁“并不是新鲜事”，没那么重要。 </p>; <p>;他告诉瑞典TT新闻社，“你可以把它看作是对个人行动的号召。如果这是他们自己组织的，他们就不会这样提前宣布。你还应该记住，基地组织如今已被大大削弱。”</p>; <p>;布鲁恩表示，基地组织的声明不会影响整体安全局势，最大的影响可能是在中东工作的丹麦和瑞典外交官，他们可能需要采取额外的预防措施。 </p>; <p>;布鲁恩的“预言”并非空穴来风。 </p>; <p>;2023年7月，激进分子在瑞典首都斯德哥尔摩一座清真寺外焚烧经书后，伊拉克抗议者冲进瑞典驻伊大使馆，驱逐了大使并烧毁了使馆。伊拉克总理苏达尼甚至因此驱逐了瑞典大使，并暂停了瑞典电信公司爱立信的工作许可。 </p>; <p>;截至目前，瑞典政府正在寻求法律手段限制近日来愈演愈烈的经书焚烧事件，以缓和与伊斯兰国家的紧张关系。然而，支持者们则提出，这可能违反该国宪法。 </p>; <h4>;<strong>;“</strong>;<strong>;他们会采取行动吗？</strong>;<strong>;”</strong>;</h4>; <p>;自2023年9月8日橄榄球世界杯开幕以来，法国一直在举办大型活动，包括查尔斯三世国王来访、教皇来访等，而这些活动将一直持续到2024年巴黎奥运会。正如法国内政部长达尔马宁在受访时感慨，“恐怖主义风险很高，重大事件接踵而至”。 </p>; <p>;达尔马宁表示，为了做好奥运会安保，法国已经增加了14000名警察和宪兵，并与多个部门合作，以应对不同的风险。 “我们已经为此努力了两年。”达尔马宁说。 </p>; <p>;伴随着恐袭预告的发出，不少民众担心极端组织是否会付诸行动。 </p>; <p>;法国情报研究中心副主任阿兰-罗迪埃在接受BFMTV采访时称，阿拉伯半岛基地组织威胁《查理周刊》两年后才采取行动，“这表明基地组织有能力等待”“当他们发出威胁时，随后往往会采取行动”。 </p>; <p>;9月28日，南方周末记者通过邮件联系到阿兰-罗迪埃，他透露了该组织的诸多细节。 </p>; <p>;阿兰-罗迪埃表示，2013年，阿拉伯半岛基地组织通过线上出版物《Inspire》公布了11名“通缉人物”，其中包括《查理周刊》漫画家斯特凡·沙邦尼尔(Stéphan·Charbonnier）。 </p>; <p>;两年后，两名自称来自基地组织的恐怖分子谢里夫·库阿奇(Cherif Kouachi) 和赛义德·库阿奇(Saïd Kouachi) 兄弟袭击了《查理周刊》，导致包括周刊主编在内的至少12人死亡，多人受伤。而肇事者之一赛义德曾于2011年在也门接受了军事式训练。 </p>; <p>;阿兰-罗迪埃认为，自2015年袭击事件以来，极端组织发起的圣战运动似乎不再把西方国家作为直接目标，而是“通过广告招募”。 </p>; <p>;“这些组织似乎没有足够的手段派遣活动分子到欧洲实施恐怖行动。我们必须确保他们的演讲不会被内生的恐怖分子所利用。”阿兰-罗迪埃说。 </p>; <p>;上海外国语大学中东研究所钮松认为，在全球协同反恐的攻势之下，基地组织的影响力大不如以前，但其仍具有实施暴力恐怖主义袭击的动机与能力。因此，此次基地组织威胁对法国与瑞典展开袭击仍不可掉以轻心。 </p>; <p>;钮松表示，事实上，包括法瑞在内的国际社会一直对基地组织的当前动向和活动能力保持高度关注和应有的警惕，不会对其口头威胁无动于衷。 </p>; <p>;也有人对这场恐袭预告持怀疑态度。 </p>; <p>;法国苏凡中心(Soufan Center)资深研究员瓦西姆·纳斯尔在接受法国《观点》杂志（Le Point）采访时呼吁，民众应该保持理性，“恐慌的时刻还没有到来”。 </p>; <p>;他认为，该杂志内容共17页，重点关注也门，对瑞典和法国的威胁只出现在第14页。 “威胁当然存在，我们必须认真对待它，但目前没有理由更加恐慌。”纳斯尔说。 </p>; <p style="font-family: 楷体, 楷体_GB2312, STKaiti;">;（南方周末实习生李金澳对本文亦有贡献）</p>; <p>;</p>; Mon, 16 Oct 2023 14:25:02 +0800 
巴赫：国际奥委会正考虑创办奥林匹克电子竞技运动会http://www.infzm.com/contents/258672 <div>;<i>;2023-10-16 14:00:00</i>;</div>;<p>;电竞能否入奥，或许不久将有一个新的答案。国际奥委会主席巴赫14日晚在这里透露，国际奥委会正在考虑创办属于电子竞技的奥林匹克运动会。 </p>; <p>;巴赫是在当晚举行的国际奥委会第141次全会开幕式上致辞时作上述表示的。他说：“我已经要求新的国际奥委会电子竞技委员会研究创办奥林匹克电子竞技运动会。”</p>; <p>;<a>;<img src="https://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/c802d6c41ee832ef334118874cf8eb40.jpeg" border="0" style="opacity: 1;" width="1000" height="564" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/c802d6c41ee832ef334118874cf8eb40.jpeg" data-key="254123">;</a>;</p>; <p>;据统计，全球有约30亿人玩电子游戏，其中超过5亿人对电子竞技特别感兴趣，包括虚拟体育和模拟体育，他们当中的大部分为34岁以下的年轻人。巴赫表示，这一点让国际奥委会非常看重，因此自2018年以来，国际奥委会一直以全方位的姿态介入电子竞技项目的发展。 </p>; <p>;巴赫说：“我们选择了一种方式，让我们既能活跃在电子竞技领域，又能忠实于一个多世纪以来我们所遵循的价值观。在电子竞技领域，价值观一直是我们不会逾越的红线。我们清晰的立场也赢得了电竞界越来越多的尊重。为了符合奥林匹克价值观，一家行业内领先的发行商对他们的一款热门游戏重新进行设计——这样玩家就可以射击目标，而不是人。”</p>; <p>;2021年，国际奥委会举办奥林匹克虚拟系列赛。这是国际奥委会在电子竞技领域的首个试点项目。基于奥林匹克虚拟系列赛的成功经验，国际奥委会在今年又举办了首届奥林匹克电子竞技周，结果大受欢迎——包括预选赛在内，电子竞技系列赛吸引了超过50万名参与者，比赛在所有频道上的直播浏览量超过600万。 </p>; <p>;巴赫说：“这是一个充满希望的开始，但这仅仅是一个开始。就像在任何运动中一样，即使在一个充满希望的开始之后，真正的比赛仍然在前面。”</p>; <p>;巴赫在当晚的致辞中还谈到了人工智能，他说:“我们的持续成功取决于我们如何拥抱不断加速发展的数字技术，特别是人工智能。这使得我们的《奥林匹克2020议程》更加紧迫——'要么改变，要么被改变'。”</p>; <p>;巴赫强调，国际奥委会必须掌握主动权，“我们必须对人工智能的机遇和风险进行全面分析，然后立即采取行动。我很高兴地告诉你们，这项工作已经在进行中。如果事情进展顺利，你们可能会在巴黎（奥运会）看到一些初步的结果”。 </p>; <p>;国际奥委会第141次全会将持续至17日。此次全会的主要议程包括就《奥林匹克宪章》修正案以及2028年洛杉矶奥运会的项目设置进行表决，选举产生若干名新的国际奥委会委员。此外，全会将对《奥林匹克2020+5议程》的中期实施情况进行评估，并听取2024年巴黎奥运会、2028年洛杉矶奥运会、2032年布里斯班奥运会、2026年米兰-科尔蒂纳丹佩佐冬奥会以及未来两届青奥会筹备工作进展的报告。 </p>; <p>;</p>; Mon, 16 Oct 2023 14:25:02 +0800 
高速服务区外来师傅修车受阻：背后是“独家经营权”带来的垄断收益丨快评http://www.infzm.com/contents/258660 <div>;<i>;2023-10-16 12:00:00</i>;</div>;<p>;If the vehicle breaks down in the highway service area, can it only be repaired by the repair shop in the service area? The employees of the maintenance shop in the service area threatened to stop the maintenance technicians hired from outside to repair the car. Is this "reasonable and legal"? </p>; <p>;According to Jimu News, a truck transporting fruit broke down and failed to start while resting in the Jiangxi Fengcheng service area of ​​the Shanghai-Kunming Expressway. After the auto repair shop in the service area said it could not repair the vehicle, the driver himself invited a technician from a nearby designated repair shop of the truck manufacturer to come to the service area to prepare for repairs. Unexpectedly, he was blocked and intimidated by the staff of the repair shop in the service area. The maintenance technician who was invited had no choice but to leave. The truck driver contacted several local repair shops, but they did not dare to arrange for personnel to go to the service area to repair the vehicle. There was no choice but for the driver to drag the car off the highway to repair it. </p>; <p>;It is not uncommon for car repairs to conflict with repair shops in expressway service areas. More than a month ago, a similar incident occurred in the Jiqing service area in Hunan. A truck driver was stopped by repairmen in the service area when he was inspecting his truck. After being told that the driver made the repairs himself, he uttered wild words. On social networks, similar complaints involving car repairs and tow truck conflicts on the highway are not the same. Some service area repair shop staff even use violence or threaten violence against drivers who repair their own cars. </p>; <p>;On the highway, can only repair shops in the service area repair cars? In an interview with the media, the person in charge of the Fengcheng service area said that the practices of the repair shop in the service area are "reasonable and legal and have laws to follow." The law the person in charge refers to refers to the provisions of the Highway Law, Highway Safety Protection Regulations and other relevant regulations that "prohibit the establishment of stalls within the scope of highways and highway land." This is obviously a misinterpretation. The so-called "setting up stalls" refers to setting up relatively fixed stalls for a long time and waiting for customers to come to your door. The purpose of prohibiting it is to avoid "damaging, polluting the highway and affecting the smooth flow of the highway." After receiving the invitation from the customer, he temporarily went on the road to repair the car, precisely to repair the vehicle as soon as possible to avoid parking on the road for a long time and to ensure the smooth flow of the road. Regardless of the definition of "setting up a stall" or the legislative purpose of the regulations, it is completely legal for drivers to repair their cars by themselves or to invite repairmen to temporarily repair their cars on the road. </p>; <p>;In the conflict at the Jiqing service area in Hunan mentioned above, the maintenance personnel in the service area claimed that the Provincial Department of Transportation has a document that stipulates that "people below" (referring to repair shops other than highways) cannot go to the highway for repairs. car, but ultimately failed to produce relevant documents. Do the traffic management departments in some places really have such regulations? If such a document does exist, it should be made public and reviewed for legality. If the government department does not have such regulations, is this an internal regulation of the highway management department, or is the service area repair shop lying? </p>; <p>;In vehicle maintenance services, drivers and car owners are consumers, and of course they have the right to freely choose repair service providers. Auto repair shops in service areas prevent drivers from repairing their cars by themselves or other repairmen, and force drivers to go to their repair shops to repair their cars. This is a "forced transaction" behavior that is expressly prohibited by the Consumer Rights Protection Act. The Criminal Law also stipulates that using violence or threats to forcefully buy or sell goods, force others to provide services or force others to receive services, if the circumstances are serious, constitutes the crime of forced transaction. </p>; <p>;Why are obviously illegal behaviors so common? The root of the problem lies in the word "profit". As the person in charge of the Fengcheng service area said, off-road vehicle maintenance personnel going to the service area to repair cars "harms the interests of the service area repair shops." The interests of service area repair shops are actually the interests of service area and highway managers. Expressway service areas, as part of expressway service facilities, are constructed and operated by expressway managers. If a repair shop opens in a service area, it must pay space rent to the highway administrator. These rents are generally higher than those for sites outside highways, because this is not only site rent, but also implies a premium for "exclusive operating rights." Precisely because highway managers also benefit from the "exclusive operating rights" of repair shops, they will naturally try their best to protect the interests of repair shops. </p>; <p>;This "exclusivity" premium is very common in closed establishments. Food prices in airport terminals and highway service areas are generally much more expensive than in urban areas. Even canteens in primary and secondary schools can be auctioned for sky-high prices. This is all due to the monopoly benefits brought by the "exclusive operating rights." More importantly, these premium benefits are not obtained through market competition, but rely on franchise rights granted by administrative power. For these infrastructure operators with administrative monopolies, the common practice in various countries is to strictly limit their profit margins to maintain a balance between attracting social investment and avoiding huge profits to maintain public welfare. To this end, they must be strictly supervised to prevent them from relying on their monopoly status to harm the public interest. </p>; <p>;A few years ago, there was an incident in a highway service area in Guangdong where a driver repaired his own car and was threatened by a repair shop employee. Due to public opinion and the intervention of relevant departments, the auto repair shop in the service area was shut down for rectification. The same incident occurred in Fengcheng, Jiangxi this time. The public expects local market supervision and other departments to take timely action to investigate and deal with forced buying and selling, and forced transactions to safeguard the interests of consumers. </p>; <p>;</p>;<br>;<hr>;<div>;Get more RSS:<br>;<a href="https://feedx.net" style="color:orange" target= "_blank">;https://feedx.net</a>; <br>;<a href="https://feedx.best" style="color:orange" target="_blank">;https://feedx. best</a>;<br>;</div>; Mon, 16 Oct 2023 12:25:03 +0800 
