an flesh". It is an act of publicly exposing the privacy of others on the Internet with the purpose of "breaking the other party's hypocrisy". It is actually an act of cyber violence that infringes on personal privacy. </p>; <p>;First of all, celebrities, like ordinary people, have the right to marry and love freely, and they can choose to do so publicly or not. Although celebrities, as public figures, will be exposed to the public eye and accept comments from the outside world, can their personal privacy be exposed at will and involuntarily? </p>; <p>;The problem of personal privacy leakage reflected in this incident is more serious than many people imagine. Nowadays, any ordinary person will receive sales calls from different banks, credit, and real estate companies every day, and the leakage of personal contact information has become a common occurrence. For celebrities, their ID numbers are almost an open secret. Taking airport pick-up and drop-off as an example, how do fans learn about a celebrity’s travel itinerary? Most of them have the ID numbers and itinerary information of celebrities, and this information usually comes from illegal "scalpers" selling it for a few yuan to dozens of yuan. </p>; <p>;<img src="https://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/18a2b1484d42333596d077e3559bf7b8.jpeg" border="0" width="617" height= "735" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/18a2b1484d42333596d077e3559bf7b8.jpeg" data-key="254122">;</p>; <p>;<img src ="https://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/208f5fa16d95e7cd3c26e368dbbbbe9a.jpeg" border="0" width="505" height="404" data-src="// images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/208f5fa16d95e7cd3c26e368dbbbbe9a.jpeg" data-key="254118">;</p>; <p>;With this information, they can not only grasp the star's schedule, They can also book air tickets and steal their mileage at will. Artists such as Li Chen, Wu Lei, and Jiang Yingrong have all experienced situations where their airplane seats were changed and their mileage was stolen. </p>; <p>;When the desire for voyeurism is infinitely magnified, some people will even use public power to satisfy such dark desires. </p>; <p>;After Chen Muchi's marriage registration information was exposed, many netizens questioned the source of the screenshots - from which channel did such detailed personal privacy information leak out? Was it the work of staff from the civil affairs system? </p>; <p>;Coincidentally, on January 31, 2023, Hu Ge announced that he was getting married and had a daughter. However, because his wife was not a public figure, Hu Ge did not disclose her identity. Someone also exposed Hu Ge's marriage registration information, allowing netizens to discover that Hu Ge's wife is a staff member close to him. </p>; <p>;<img src="https://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/ae1f0a396113d36fa7ceeb8745b50d52.jpeg" border="0" width="640" height= "630" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/ae1f0a396113d36fa7ceeb8745b50d52.jpeg" data-key="254117">;</p>; <p>;If you have a lawyer Popular Science: In real life, no matter lawyers, courts, public security, or procuratorates, they cannot access citizens’ information at will. Citizens’ private information must not be accessed or leaked for non-public needs. Any access will leave traces. </p>; <p>;<img src="https://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/26785e53c02b4b9149ebd6f7b7a5f1bc.jpeg" border="0" width="640" height= "791" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/26785e53c02b4b9149ebd6f7b7a5f1bc.jpeg" data-key="254120">;</p>; <p>;In order to respond to a Celebrities are "hunting" for privacy, and abusing their power, ignoring the law, and wantonly spreading personal privacy is the most terrifying part of the whole thing. The act of spreading other people's privacy based on the mentality of taking advantage of others will not only cause secondary harm to the victim, but is actually illegal. </p>; <p>;Article 1032, paragraph 1, of the Civil Code stipulates: "Natural persons enjoy the right to privacy. No organization or individual may infringe on the privacy rights of others by means of spying, intrusion, disclosure, disclosure, etc." The right to privacy protects the privacy of natural persons. It can be seen from the word privacy itself that it has two characteristics: one is "hidden", that is, it is not a public state. If it has been disclosed by a natural person on his own or legally disclosed, it is not private; the second is "private", That is, private matters have nothing to do with other people's rights and interests, public interests, etc. It is from these two aspects that Article 1032, Paragraph 2 of the Civil Code defines privacy as: "A natural person's private life is peaceful and he does not want others to know about his private space, private activities, and private information."< /p>; <p>;Article 1033 of the Civil Code stipulates that, unless otherwise provided by law or with the explicit consent of the right holder, no organization or individual may commit the following acts:</p>; <p>;( 1) Intruding on the private life and peace of others through phone calls, text messages, instant messaging tools, emails, leaflets, etc.;</p>; <p>;(2) Entering, photographing, and peeping into other people's homes, hotel rooms, and other private spaces;< /p>; <p>;(3) Photographing, peeping, eavesdropping, and disclosing the private activities of others;</p>; <p>;(4) Photographing, peeping at the private parts of others’ bodies;</p>; <p>;(5) Process other people's private information;</p>; <p>;(6) Infringe on the privacy rights of others in other ways. </p>; <p>;No matter whether you love or hate a person, you should not use the "open box" method to make other people's legally protected privacy and personal information public, and you must never do anything illegal. Blind tolerance and helplessness will only encourage the voyeurs' desire for control and arrogance, allowing them to hide in dark corners and continue to do whatever they want. </p>; <p>;Whether you are a celebrity or an ordinary person, your right to privacy is protected by law. Legal experts also emphasized that when the legitimate rights and interests enjoyed are illegally infringed, one should immediately call the police and use legal weapons to protect one's own rights and interests. </p>; <p>;</p>;<br>;<hr>;<div>;Get more RSS:<br>;<a href="https://feedx.net" style="color:orange" target= "_blank">;https://feedx.net</a>; <br>;<a href="https://feedx.best" style="color:orange" target="_blank">;https://feedx. best</a>;<br>;</div>; Mon, 16 Oct 2023 11:25:03 +0800 
