“两弹一星”元勋钱学森｜那年今日http://www.infzm.com/contents/258622 <div>;<i>;2023-10-16 10:00:00</i>;</div>; Mon, 16 Oct 2023 10:25:03 +0800 
“灵神星”探测器升空：星际采矿还是建立基地？http://www.infzm.com/contents/258664 <div>;<i>;2023-10-16 09:00:00</i>;</div>;<p>;October 13, 2023, 10:19 U.S. Eastern Time (22:19 Beijing time on the same day), carrying NASA The SpaceX "Falcon Heavy" launch vehicle of the "Psyche" probe was successfully launched from the 39A launch pad of the Cape Canaveral Space Launch Base. The probe successfully entered orbit. The two first stages of the launch vehicle All thrusters were recovered and the launch mission was a complete success. </p>; <p>;However, the whole mission has just begun. According to NASA: The probe will have to fly 2.2 billion miles (nearly 3.6 billion kilometers) to reach "16 Psyche" in the main asteroid belt between Mars and Jupiter in 2029, and orbit the asteroid for 26 months. scientific investigation. </p>; <p>;The magnetometer on board the probe will search for evidence of the asteroid's ancient magnetic field to prove the theory that it is the remnant of a fragmented planet's core. Gamma-ray and neutron spectrometers will help scientists determine the chemical elements that make up asteroids. A multispectral imager will provide information about its mineral composition and its topography. </p>; <p>;This exploration mission includes many first-of-its-kind scientific and technological innovations: This is the first time a human spacecraft has used Hall-effect thrusters (electromagnetic propulsion) in deep space beyond the lunar orbit. vehicle), driven almost entirely by solar energy, flew to the junction of the inner solar system and the outer solar system; it was also the first time for humans to explore the first M-type asteroid metallic body. </p>; <p>;NASA emphasized: This project is the result of comprehensive cooperation between the American scientific community and industry. The main research team is led by Lindy Elkins-Tanton of Arizona State University, and more than a dozen other universities and research institutions participate. The Jet Propulsion Laboratory and Caltech in Southern California assist NASA with scientific management, systems engineering, integration and testing, and mission operations. Maxar Technologies' team in California is responsible for the solar power system and the "Hall electric pusher". SpaceX's Falcon Heavy launch vehicle is responsible for the probe launch mission. </p>; <p>;In addition to NASA's scientific expedition mission, this project is of great significance to the future development of mankind. It can be said to be the first step in the exploration journey of "interstellar mining". </p>; <p>;"16 Psyche" is located in the asteroid belt between Mars and Jupiter. It was discovered by the Italian astronomer Gasparis on March 17, 1852. It was named after "Greek mythology" by humans. Named after Psyche, the wife of the soul and Eros, the god of love. </p>; <p>;The long axis of its ellipsoidal body is 225 kilometers, and it is almost entirely made of metal. Its mass is astonishingly large, about 272 million tons, accounting for about 0.6% of the total mass of celestial bodies in the "asteroid belt".这颗小行星的金属比重达82.5%，主要成份是铁、镍，以及黄金、铂、铜等贵金属。 "Forbes" and others value it at between US$1 billion and US$100 billion. </p>; <p>;Scientists are curious: Why is the metal content of this asteroid so high? One theory is that it is the remnant core of an early planet in the early stages of the formation of the solar system. During the growth process of a planet, it was hit by other celestial bodies, and its outer crust and mantle were shattered into countless fragments, leaving only bare metal material. The original planetary core. The reason for this speculation is that the small "Psyche" actually has two large impact craters, and there is no sign of water or hydrated minerals on its surface. </p>; <p>;Currently, human research on the planet’s core is still extremely limited. We have not even drilled through 1/3 of the thin crust, the outermost layer of the Earth’s structure. Research on the mantle and core can only be done. Make inferences based on seismic waves. If "Spirit Star" is indeed proven to be a rocky planetary core, then this cooled planetary core will allow humans to intuitively understand the structure of the planet's core and gain a deeper understanding of the planet's origin, evolution, and development. This will further promote the rapid development of geophysical research. </p>; <p>;NASA’s launch of a probe to the “Spirit Star” is undoubtedly paving the way for the commercialization of space resources in the future. This kind of investment in technology and capital is very long-term. Just like Prince Enrique in the early days of the "Great Navigation", he continued to invest in the ocean for decades, but it took several generations for the Portuguese royal family to get feedback from the ocean. </p>; <p>;With human aerospace technology, the cost of mining from extraterrestrials and transporting it back to earth will be so high that 1 kilogram of pig iron is more expensive than the same weight of top-quality diamonds. So, why do NASA and Musk conduct such research and exploration? </p>; <p>;The author believes that their idea is not to smelt iron on the "Ling Shen" and then send it back to the earth, but to "colonize Mars". "Ling Shen" is extremely far away from the earth, but relatively close to Mars. "Mars colonization" requires a large amount of building materials. If iron, nickel and other metals from "Spirit Star" are used, it will be much cheaper than transporting materials from the earth to Mars. </p>; <p>;Iron and nickel are the basic materials for making stainless steel. Using solar energy, space metallurgy is directly performed in a vacuum space environment. The production process is completely different from that on the earth, and no carbon-based energy and catalysts are needed. Musk insists on exploring the application of stainless steel in his "Starship" research and development, rather than the carbon fiber aerospace materials used by other countries. This can be explained logically: they have considered the selection of materials for large-scale infrastructure and manufacturing on extraterrestrial planets. question. </p>; <p>;Musk has also invested in Solar City to develop solar energy. This can be explained by NASA taking great technical risks to use solar-powered "Hall thrusters" in the "Psyche" mission. pass. In the asteroid belt between Mars and Jupiter, solar radiation is already weak, so why choose a less efficient solar drive? It seems that NASA is exploring technology to improve the efficiency of its use under the conditions of low solar energy in deep space. This is the exploratory spirit of "knowing that there are tigers in the mountains, and prefer to travel to the tiger mountains", which shows his great determination, firm will and actions. </p>; <p>;When I was young, I played the video game "StarCraft", and "interstellar mining" was the first step in building a base. Unexpectedly, before reaching old age, human beings have already begun to try to realize their dreams. It can be said that thousands of sails are racing against each other and hundreds of teams are competing against each other. The vision of humanity becoming a space-faring species is getting closer. </p>; <p>;<span style="color: #ba1010;">;•</span>;<span style="font-family: Kaiti, Kaiti_GB2312, STKaiti; font-weight: bold;">;（ This article is only the author's personal opinion and does not represent the position of this newspaper)</span>;</p>; <p>;</p>; Mon, 16 Oct 2023 09:55:02 +0800 
“飞越”按摩店：两位盲人的择业折返跑http://www.infzm.com/contents/258668 <div>;<i>;2023-10-16 08:00:00</i>;</div>;<p>;<img alt="Blind masseur Sun Jingrui is massaging a customer. Photo by Wang Xinyi" src="http:/ /images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/34b826dd72.png" border="0" width="1080" height="607" data-src="//images.infzm.com /cms/medias/image/23/10/15/34b826dd72.png" data-key="254113">;</p>; <p style="color: #999999; text-align: center;">;Blind masseur Sun Jingrui is massaging a customer. Photo by Wang Xinyi</p>; <p>;Ren Wenfeng's 15-year career as a blind masseur can be divided into two periods: in the first period he struggled with "what can a blind person do", and in the latter period was he answering "what can I do". </p>; <p>;The interval was a two-year escape - in 2019, he decided to escape from the blind employment paradigm and worked as a barista and telephone recruiter in Guangzhou. </p>; <p>;At about the same time, another blind masseur, Sun Jingrui, also chose to run away. After they briefly crossed paths in Guangzhou, the two lifelines bifurcated again, but they ended up reaching the same destination. </p>; <p>;At the age of 31, Ren Wenfeng returned to his hometown of Huanggang, Hubei Province and reopened a massage parlor in the small county town. He and his wife manage the small shop, which is about 40 square meters, and entertain three or four customers every day. </p>; <p>;34-year-old Sun Jingrui also returned to the massage parlor, but he chose to work in the metropolis Guangzhou. His store is also closer to the consumption perception of modern urbanites: warm yellow lighting, the fragrance of essential oils, supplemented by Mindfulness meditation.客人不太多时，静睿会写方案，或是外出对接资源，像一个创业者那样，思索着如何打造更多连锁店。 </p>; <p>;According to data from the China Disabled Persons' Federation, as of 2020, there are 17,300 blind health massage institutions in China. In the common discussion of "What can blind people do without massages?" Ren Wenfeng and Sun Jingrui may have many answers to this question, but one thing is for sure, although returning to a massage parlor may not seem to fit the mainstream narrative, it is Doesn't mean "failed". </p>; <h4>;Falling into Darkness</h4>; <p>;Ren Wenfeng and Sun Jingrui are both acquired blind people, which means that they need one more layer of psychological construction than congenitally blind people. They want to eliminate all their once-visible selves, as well as their past thoughts, and learn to live in darkness from scratch. </p>; <p>;When he was 8 years old, a wooden stick flew in while playing and changed the direction of Ren Wenfeng’s life. The surgery failed to save his vision, and retinal detachment was a gradual farewell, which was more painful than a sudden plunge into darkness. </p>; <p>;He began to worry about his future life: Will he have to rely on his parents for the rest of his life? How will I support myself in the future? These questions all point to the same thing: What can a blind person do? </p>; <p>;One day during the summer vacation, he listened to a radio program that introduced summer training classes to people. He called and asked: "What can blind people do?" The other party told him that he should contact the local Disabled Persons' Federation. </p>; <p>;In comparison, the process of Sun Jingrui's blindness is like a person struggling in the water. When he was in junior high school, he was diagnosed with retinal detachment.因为发现较晚，手术难以逆转损伤，这几乎等同于宣判失明。 The doctor suggested that he go to a school for the blind to adapt to his future outcome in advance. </p>; <p>;But Sun Jingrui decided to race against his eyesight. He wanted to get into a good university before he lost his sight, so that he could "choose a major that is not too hard on the eyes and continue to live a normal life." Before suffering from eye disease, Sun Jingrui’s dream was to major in mechanical engineering at South China University of Technology. This was a place where he could realize his dream of becoming an engineer. But in his sophomore year of high school, the fog in front of his eyes became thicker and thicker. </p>; <p>;2006 was the year of Sun Jingrui's college entrance examination. The girl he had a crush on would call him and ask him "When will he come back to class?" She had sorted out the class content and was waiting for him. Sun Jingrui said vaguely "next month." </p>; <p>;Sun Jingrui could not wait until the day he returned to the classroom. With the disappearance of the last bit of light, he became completely blind. He no longer dares to go out for fear that others will notice the strangeness of his eyeballs. Occasionally, once he goes out every few months, he will outline the surrounding environment in his mind and turn his head frequently, trying to act like he was before he lost his sight. </p>; <p>;For discerning people, career planning is a process of continuous focus: "study-weigh-choose", and finally choose the track you are best at. But for blind people, massage parlors are one of the most common secular choices and one of the few stable careers for this special group. </p>; <p>;Blind massage parlors are like blind paths in the city, existing but not noticeable. They are scattered throughout the city, set up at street intersections, on the first floor of residential buildings, or between barber shops and grocery stores. Most stores are simply furnished, with a few lamps, a few beds, and one or two chairs placed in fixed locations. </p>; <p>;Ren Wenfeng’s first massage parlor job was in Wuhan, and he was contacted by the Disabled Persons’ Federation in his hometown. The massage shop is located on the second floor of a residential area. Four beds and two sofas are squeezed into the 20-square-meter house. At night, he called his mother and complained: "It's too shabby. I want to turn around and leave."</p>; <p>;But he persisted in the end: "As long as there is a job that a blind person can do, anything can be done."< /p>; <p>;In 2011, Ren Wenfeng came to Shanghai from Wuhan. When customers at the massage parlor talked about urban life, Ren Wenfeng stood aside with envy. In his world, the busiest moment in Shanghai is the store celebration in June. The heat wave carries the crowds, sending the noise and footsteps into the store. The masseurs are busy amidst the waves of people's voices and the sounds of watches. . After the store celebration, the crowd dispersed, leaving the masseur in the dark. </p>; <p>;Most of the time is monotonous: working from 8 a.m. to 11 p.m., food and accommodation are included in the store, and most of the time is spent waiting. Time just slipped between the thick and deformed fingers. In the view of Ren Wenfeng at the time, "This is a job with no future, or even a present." </p>; <p>;任文峰第一次工作时，那双骨节分明、纤细柔软的手，被人评价为“一双可以用来弹钢琴的手”；现在，从事按摩业十年有余，任文峰的手指变得像擀面杖一样厚重，“专门干按摩这一行的手”，有人这么夸奖他。 </p>; <p>;Now, Sun Jingrui has also noticed changes in his body. The muscles on the back of the hand are broad and thick, and the top of the thumb nail is slightly buckled due to years of exertion. The skin connected to the nail has shed its skin and is slightly white. In Guangzhou, he relieves the pressure on the shoulders and necks of many white-collar workers who sit in offices for a long time, but his own cervical vertebrae are tingling due to long-term fixed posture massage. </p>; <p>;Sun Jingrui is unwilling to live in a traditional massage shop. Pictures of the lives of discerning people in the past remind him from time to time. If he cannot return to the world of discerning people, he must at least make achievements in the massage industry. </p>; <p>;<img alt="Sun Jingrui's thumb tip is peeling. Photo by Wang Xinyi" src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/537b790619 .png" border="0" width="1080" height="877" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/537b790619.png" data-key ="254114">;</p>; <p style="color: #999999; text-align: center;">;Sun Jingrui’s thumb tip is peeling. Photo by Wang Xinyi</p>; <h4>;Beyond Making a Living</h4>; <p>;The Internet is one of the common channels for visually impaired people to contact the outside world. </p>; <p>;At the end of 2018, Ren Wenfeng learned about the "Coffee in the Palm" project of Hemu Innovation Center, a non-profit organization in Guangzhou, through an online forum. This is an activity to train visually impaired people to learn hand-brewed coffee skills and become baristas. As the road was being built in front of the store and business was not booming, Ren Wenfeng closed the massage parlor operating in Wuhan and went to Guangzhou to study. </p>; <p>;Liu Yingzhang, the head of Hemu Innovation Center, was deeply impressed by him: "I resigned from Wuhan and occasionally do some part-time jobs to supplement my income."</p>; <p>;In 2019, Sun Jingrui also used the Internet to The community gained access to the "Dialogue Academy" project organized by "Dialogue in the Dark", a Hong Kong social enterprise. He sold the massage parlor he was running and went to Hong Kong alone for training as one of the six members who passed the interview. </p>; <p>;Unlike Ren Wenfeng who started his career with massage, Sun Jingrui had the consciousness of entering the "mainstream workplace" when he just lost his eyesight. With good English, he once sought opportunities to work as an interpreter through a hotline program on a radio station. This experience ended in failure, which shattered his illusions about employment for the visually impaired. Returning to the field of massage, he also considered entering a hospital. But "total blindness" once again prevented him from getting a stable and decent job. </p>; <p>;The problem goes far beyond that. Finding a position that accepts visually impaired people is the first step. After entering the workplace, the challenge really begins. </p>; <p>;After becoming blind, more than ten years of experience in massage parlors affected Ren Wenfeng's character. Sensitivity and low self-esteem were the biggest challenges he faced in the "mainstream workplace". When he was a barista, some customers would initiate conversations, but he could only respond with silence. In Ren Wenfeng's narration, his perception of the "mainstream world" is contradictory: like a mirror: on the polished surface facing outward, he wants to be recognized and prove that he "can also accomplish many things"; on the coated surface It is his timidity, he is afraid that others will notice his "difference". </p>; <p>;In Hong Kong, in order to adapt to the teacher's rhythm and language environment, Sun Jingrui needs to listen to class recordings repeatedly. "Going to bed at two or three in the morning, and getting up again at six or seven in the morning, because class starts at eight." During the course, he was deeply touched by two parts. The first part is "self-advocacy", where visually impaired students learn how to seek help in the workplace; the second part is skills training, including holding regular meetings, taking notes, organizing activities, etc. These ordinary people's daily work content is very new in Sun Jingrui's eyes. "There is no such thing in a massage parlor." </p>; <p>;When visually impaired people choose other jobs, they always subconsciously compare them with the massage industry. They use the massage industry as a frame of reference to view the world. </p>; <p>;In the practical part of the course in Hong Kong, Sun Jingrui needed to design workshops and course content alone in a social enterprise. With the help of his instructor, he gradually grew from an initial "facilitator" to an "implementer" of the project. By". He gradually discovered: "I can actually do a lot of things."</p>; <p>;Different from Sun Jingrui's discovery of "what he can do" in the workplace, Ren Wenfeng's experience as a barista made him discover "what he cannot or cannot do" What do you like to do?" Looking back now, Ren Wenfeng feels that knowing "what not to do" is the beginning of career planning - in this sense, although he failed to become an excellent barista, this experience is not a failure. </p>; <p>;Due to the limited income of a barista, Ren Wenfeng wanted to do something else. His second job is telephone recruitment: 30 phone calls a day that last for more than 30 seconds, corresponding to a basic salary of more than 1,000 yuan; if the other party is willing to submit a resume and successfully joins the job, he will receive a commission. According to Ren Wenfeng's rough statistics, the call answering rate is about 50%, which means that at least 60 calls need to be made every day. What is more difficult to control is that most of the answerers will hang up the phone in about 10 seconds. Rejection is normal, and what makes Ren Wenfeng even more unbearable are those unfriendly words. After a few months, Ren Wenfeng's performance was at the bottom of the group because he was not good at speaking. </p>; <p>;At that time, Sun Jingrui also experienced telephone recruitment work. He summarized the job as "repetitive" and "boring": "I keep saying repetitive words every day, and even get scolded."</p>; p>; <p>;In the view of Guo Siyuan, a teacher at the School of Humanities and Social Sciences of the Zhongkai College of Agricultural Engineering: "The uneven quality of education for blind people is the pain point that restricts the employment of people with disabilities." Ren Wenfeng also described the problems encountered in the "mainstream workplace" The embarrassment is attributed to the lack of education. Blind people only need to learn the skills of living. As for spiritual nourishment and interpersonal communication skills such as literature, history and philosophy, it seems not so important. </p>; <p>;<img alt="Sun Jingrui's "Healing Time" store uses warm yellow as the main color. Photo by Wang Xinyi" src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/ 10/15/da8b8d691c.png" border="0" width="1080" height="608" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/da8b8d691c. png" data-key="254115">;</p>; <p style="color: #999999; text-align: center;">;Sun Jingrui's "Healing Time" store uses warm yellow as the main color. Photo by Wang Xinyi</p>; <h4>;“Seeing” myself</h4>; <p>;At the end of 2021, after returning to Huanggang from Guangzhou, Ren Wenfeng started a family. Now the massage parlor he runs is facing the road, with a small yard behind it. Although it cannot be seen, he bought green plants and table lamps and carefully arranged this imaginary space. In his free time, he would make himself a cup of coffee with the sound of wind chimes and sunshine, waiting for customers and learning something new at the same time. </p>; <p>;“I returned to the massage parlor because I didn’t feel safe enough.” Ren Wenfeng said, “Many jobs are not only unstable, but may also have no income at all.” The stable income brought by massage parlors means that he Be able to feel more confident in front of parents, loved ones and neighbors. </p>; <p>;"Take what you have learned back and open a store. This may be Wenfeng's most practical choice." Liu Yingzhang said. </p>; <p>;Compared with the rush of big cities, small cities are more casual. The guests communicated with Ren Wenfeng about the details of the massage in their hometown dialect. Sometimes Ren Wenfeng would take the initiative to ask the guests "does it hurt?" He was no longer content to be a silent backdrop. </p>; <p>;Sun Jingrui’s store in Guangzhou opened in 2022. The store staff are partners who met during charity activities, and are supported by startup resources from the Hemu Innovation Center. The concept of the store is to use mindfulness to guide customers to observe their bodies, highlighting the masseurs Masseurs gain recognition through their professional skills and techniques, and no longer rely on selling essential oils and other peripheral products to gain value. </p>; <p>;In the view of colleague Zhang Jinlan, Sun Jingrui's attempt to break through traditional massage parlors is "very meaningful." Many customers will give gifts to the visually impaired masseuses in return, and will also hold their hands and show them the gifts. </p>; <p>;White-collar workers like to call Jing Rui by his English name Ray, and some customers call him "dolphin". He said he likes this nickname: when humans are drowning, dolphins will lift humans to the surface of the water. In daily life, Jingrui is willing to enlighten his visually impaired friends and lift them out of the "ocean" of emotions.每当张金兰在工作上遇到难点时，孙静睿就会罗列出要点，逐条和她讲道理，“他是一个可以并肩作战的伙伴”。 </p>; <p>;孙静睿希望帮助更多的视障人士到外面看看，但单枪匹马的“托举”往往有些无力。他不太好意思直接劝，有时会采取“迂回战术”，比如，故作轻松和朋友说：“明天有一个演讲俱乐部，谁有空一起过去玩一下？”朋友们会觉得很新奇，但是一到真的要上台表演的时候，他们又觉得“太害羞了，不行的”。 </p>; <p>;孙静睿也曾面临这样的困境。在刘颖璋看来，孙静睿算是这一群体的“精英”。第一次来到该中心参加活动时，孙静睿戴着墨镜，用一口流利的英语和大家打招呼，这种“大哥”气质当时就给刘颖璋留下了很深的印象。 </p>; <p>;在工作中，孙静睿最初也有“依靠明眼人管理者”的思维惯性。目前，合木创新中心的“手心咖啡”和“愈时间”按摩店项目都由视障人士担任管理者，独立带领视障与非视障的员工，共同参与市场竞争，这和以往由非视障人士领导的模式有本质不同。他们希望这种模式能够打破视障者只能在职场中扮演从属者的偏见，有一天，只需稍加引导，他们能主动探索世界。 </p>; <p>;<img alt="孙静睿在网络上广为流传的个人照。网络图片" src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/bd761597be.png" border="0" width="1080" height="1264" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/bd761597be.png" data-key="254116">;</p>; <p style="color: #999999; text-align: center;">;孙静睿在网络上广为流传的个人照。网络图片</p>; <p>;在网络上流传较广的一张照片中，孙静睿身着白衬衫、牛仔裤，戴着墨镜，一只手托着下巴，露出标志性露齿笑。但他记忆中自己的形象，却停留在18岁之前，静睿的梦想是未来有一天，他的视力恢复了，能够亲眼看看身边伙伴的模样，也能看看自己穿上职业装是什么样子。 </p>; <p>;<span style="color: #ba1010;">;• </span>;<strong>;<strong>;<span style="font-family: 楷体, 楷体_GB2312, STKaiti; font-weight: bold;">;（陈鑫、刘颖璋和深度训练营对本文亦有贡献）</span>;</strong>;</strong>;</p>; <p>;</p>; Mon, 16 Oct 2023 08:25:03 +0800 
我们该以什么姿态面对“牺牲者”丨记者手记http://www.infzm.com/contents/258658 <div>;<i>;2023-10-15 23:00:00</i>;</div>;<p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/z03yFnCJiTOLmMoGQ3hWWPydrAH9HG48GZcsUjV2.jpg" border="0" width="1063" height="681" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/z03yFnCJiTOLmMoGQ3hWWPydrAH9HG48GZcsUjV2.jpg" data-key="254109">;</p>; <p style="color: #999; text-align: center;">;年轻时的何协（左）与朋友。<span style="color: #aaa;">;（受访者供图/图）</span>;</p>; <p>;2023年7月，我去了内蒙古根河市郊的敖鲁古雅鄂温克自治乡采访，使鹿鄂温克人已经搬迁到那儿整20年了。这场搬迁，对鄂温克人来说，最大的变化就是禁枪。这意味着他们传统游猎生活的终结。</p>; <p>;我在乡里闲晃，和人谈起枪的事，边上的看客马上给我指路：这得找何老大啊，还有谁能比他更清楚？语气里隐约带有些揶揄的味道——在当时，我并不清楚这里头有什么故事。</p>; <p>;找到何老大也不难，大多数时候，他都和妻子卓耶在家门口的长凳上安静地坐着。</p>; <p>;何老大的本名叫何协，“中国最后一位女酋长”玛力亚索的大儿子，鄂温克人里最后一代猎民。一到他家门前，他就招呼我坐下，还给我开了瓶海拉尔啤酒，这是他的待客之道。</p>; <p>;后来我才知道，枪在去年刚给何协惹来麻烦。2003年前后收枪时，他私藏了把小口径枪，2022年卖给了别人。被人举报后，法院以倒卖枪支罪判刑。何协搞不清判决书是怎么写的，就记得“判二缓三”，退休金也没了。</p>; <p>;好在，何协也没那么在乎钱，够用就行了嘛。两口子靠卓耶每月四千多的退休金过活，是“月光族”。</p>; <p>;何协的一位朋友和我讲起不久前发生的事。前段时间，何协向他借了500块，说是要拿去还钱。结果，何协还了一百多块的账，剩下的钱全买了卤牛肉和啤酒。三百多买的肉，两口子没吃几筷子，全拿去喂了乡里的狗。“这不是糟蹋钱吗？”提起这事，这位朋友多少还有些生气。他也拿何协没辙，“这家伙，倒是什么也不操心！”</p>; <p>;何协的一些举动也的确让人无可奈何。采访期间，我和何协等人一起回了趟搬迁前的老敖乡，当晚在附近民宿住宿。即便民宿大堂醒目地贴着请勿吸烟的告示，何协还是旁若无人地抽起烟来。同行者劝他出去抽，他又犟上了：抽根烟怎么了？现代社会的规矩在他那儿基本是失效的。民宿老板只得再三叮嘱我们，一定要看住何协，房间里可绝对不能抽烟。</p>; <p>;在敖乡，他成了“没进步”的一类人。内蒙古社科院民族研究所研究员白兰关注鄂温克人已有三十多年，和何协一家成了老友。她和我讲起，2023年7月，她去敖乡参加一场旅游论坛。碰到何协时，他已经喝到差不多了。乡长赶紧让工作人员把他送回了家，“那么多领导来，（担心）何协搁那儿丢人”。</p>; <p>;离开敖乡前，我打算去和何协告个别。一进门，他正躺在屋里闷着头睡觉呢。卓耶告诉我，何协已经在床上躺了一整天，前两天有客人来，高兴，又喝猛了。</p>; <p>;回到北京后，我读了纪录片导演顾桃写的《敖鲁古雅·敖鲁古雅》，这是他拍摄“鄂温克三部曲”时的日记合集。书里描写的何协同我见到的完全是两副模样。</p>; <p>;在顾桃的书里，他是山上猎民点神气的“点儿长”。“锯鹿茸时，何协总要对着喷血的茸喝上几口，眼睛眯成缝，卷卷的头发，脸上还溅着血滴，别人看了会吓一跳，他却很享受。”</p>; <p>;在猎民点，何协的气场能镇住那些偷酒喝的人。“维佳和毛谢（二人都是鄂温克猎民）没有去找鹿，而是搭上顺风车去阿龙山找酒了。中午毛谢和维佳醉醺醺地回来，看到何老大，都悄悄躲回自己家的帐篷睡去了”。“只要何协在点上，玛力亚索就不会担心”。</p>; <p>;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;我忍不住想，要是他们还有枪，还能上山打猎，何协会不会和现在的状态不一样？当然，这只是个无效的假设。只有一两百人的使鹿鄂温克人，融入现代化进程中，是早晚都会发生的事情。而其中总有一两代人，会成为这一进程中的牺牲者。他们上一代，完整地享受了山林中的生活，而下一代，没那么多包袱，又探索出了新的活法。</p>; <p>;有学者认为，从国家治理的层面上看，这是必须要做出的牺牲。理性的态度是，记住牺牲的那部分人，给予他们及后代一定的补偿，“这才是现实”。</p>; <p>;&nbsp;白兰说，她一直在思考，怎么让鄂温克人在发展过程中，有更多自主选择权，让传统得以延续。不过，她到现在，还是没有结论。“作为研究者，有时候我感觉自己是失败的。”听到白兰说出这句话，我心里咯噔一下。&nbsp;</p>; <p>;作为记者，我能做的，只能是记录下“牺牲者”如今的生活状态，抵抗遗忘。</p>; <p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/CoPO3sir3sJ83J1WYSZA9THj2LsdK3ILWHYsS49V.jpg" border="0" width="1073" height="771" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/10/15/CoPO3sir3sJ83J1WYSZA9THj2LsdK3ILWHYsS49V.jpg" data-key="254108">;</p>; <p style="color: #999; text-align: center;">;2023年7月23日傍晚，何协坐在定居点的马路牙子上喝酒。<span style="color: #aaa;">;（南方周末记者韩谦/图）</span>;</p>; <p>;</p>; Sun, 15 Oct 2023 23:25:03 +0800
